.TH F00-ID 1 "2026" "f00 0.15.7" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
f00\-id \- print real and effective user and group IDs (f00tils)
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B f00\-id
[\fIOPTION\fR]... [\fIUSER\fR]
.SH DESCRIPTION
Print user and group information for the specified USER, or for the
current process if no USER is given. Pure assembly multicall. MIT.
.PP
Default is modern mode.
.B \-\-core
selects strict GNU id\-compatible output.
.SH COREUTILS FLAGS
.TP
\fB\-u\fR, \fB\-\-user\fR
print only the effective user ID
.TP
\fB\-g\fR, \fB\-\-group\fR
print only the effective group ID
.TP
\fB\-G\fR, \fB\-\-groups\fR
print all group IDs
.TP
\fB\-n\fR, \fB\-\-name\fR
print a name instead of a number (for \-ugG)
.PP
See
.B f00\-id \-\-help
for the full flag list.
.SH MODERN FLAGS
.TP
\fB\-\-core\fR
strict coreutils\-compatible output
.TP
\fB\-j\fR, \fB\-\-json\fR
JSON identity summary
.TP
\fB\-\-csv\fR
CSV identity summary
.SH AUTHOR
f00 contributors. License MIT.
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR id (1),
.BR f00\-whoami (1),
.BR f00\-groups (1),
.BR f00 (1)
.PP
https://f00.sh
